# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-58644
# Product:   sharepoint_server
# Tags:      [KEV] [RCE] [CRIT]
# Score:     120
# Tier:      CRITICAL — ACT NOW
# Generated: 2026-07-22T03:08:52.996483Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only. The advisory [4] describes unauthenticated HTTP requests
# targeting SharePoint endpoints as the initial attack vector, consistent with
# the NVD description [1] of deserialization of untrusted data over the network
# (AV:N/PR:N/UI:N, CVSS 9.8 [1]). The CISA KEV entry [3] and VulnCheck KEV
# listing [2] confirm active in-the-wild exploitation as of 2026-07-14/16.
# Specific serialized payload byte sequences, request paths, or HTTP headers
# unique to CVE-2026-58644 exploits are NOT available without PCAP or PoC data.
# The content/pcre matches below target .NET BinaryFormatter / ViewState
# serialization artefacts commonly associated with SharePoint deserialization
# attacks and HTTP request patterns noted in the Resecurity advisory [4], but
# HAVE NOT been validated against captured exploit traffic.
#
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline — this
# pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# ANALYST ACTION REQUIRED before any deployment:
#   1. Validate match logic against actual SharePoint exploit traffic or PoC
#      once available.
#   2. Tune or suppress rule against known-good SharePoint serialization traffic
#      to reduce false positives.
#   3. Review CISA BOD 26-04 patching requirements [3] — patching is the
#      primary mitigation for this actively exploited vulnerability.
alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-58644 Microsoft SharePoint unauthenticated deserialization RCE attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"POST";
  http.uri; content:"/_layouts/"; nocase;
  pcre:"/\/_layouts\/[^\s]*\.(aspx|ashx)/i";
  http.request_body;
  content:"|00 01 00 00 00|"; offset:0; depth:5;
  reference:cve,2026-58644;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev true, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000004; rev:1; )

